ethod regarding type and reflection. I should check if DEROctetString is available in bcprov since it feels like something might be off with the metadata in relation to native image testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing reachability metadata and test rules**\\n\\nI’m reflecting on the user rules that state not to modify reachability metadata since it’s handled externally by Forge. So, if tests exercise dynamic access, the metadata must be generated externally. That seems fine. I wonder about the mention of \\\"resolved target test source root\\\" under `src/test/java`—we’re actually inside `tests/src/.../src/test/java`. Should I not edit the Bcutil placeholder? It seems like the top-level public rule might be unrelated, but I’m unsure. I'm considering whether to revert the Bcutil_jdk18onTest edit, keeping in mind that it could violate the rules about public test classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test class visibility**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the existing setup would fail anyway. Maybe the rules haven’t been enforced yet. Since the scaffold from the generator is package-private, all top-level test classes must be public according to the coding instructions. Our added class follows this rule. It’s puzzling because I thought I had to change it, but editing the placeholder might seem unrelated. Perhaps it’s better to revert that change since the final diff would only show the new file. If the reviewer notices the existing package-private wasn't altered, that could be alright.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_N2cvPE0OqHtsdfbSk8ABazXS|fc_0ece77a3794c4c86016a25d6e2511481979ea02c34a90908b8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short && find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java -type f -print | sort"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"git status --short && find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java -type f -print | sort\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses"